\[\frac{(y^2 - 2xy)(5(x^2 + y^2) + 2xy)}{4(x^2 + y^2)} = \frac{(z^2 - 2yz)(5(y^2 + z^2) + 2yz)}{4(y^2 + z^2)}.\]This simplifies to
